        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 9:22PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 922 PM MDT/1022 PM CDT/, the public reported strong thunderstorms
along a line extending from 9 miles southeast of Brewster to 9 miles
west of Winona to near Wallace. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Wallace around 925 PM MDT.
Winona around 1030 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of these storms include Russell Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
